xbrli:xbrl.in-capmkt:MechanismsToPreventAdverseCons:
We maintain a strict zero-tolerance approach toward any form of retaliation or adverse consequences faced by individuals who raise genuine concerns. Through regular interactions and clearly defined reporting mechanisms, we ensure that all concerns are heard, respected, and addressed with due diligence. To support this commitment, we have established and implemented:
} A comprehensive Whistleblower Policy, enabling employees and stakeholders to report unethical behaviour,
misconduct, or violations confidentially and without fear.
} A robust Prevention of Sexual Harassment (PoSH) Policy, ensuring a safe and respectful workplace for all.
All grievances are managed in accordance with the highest standards of fairness, confidentiality, and integrity, reflecting our commitment to ethical business practices and a culture of transparency and accountability.

xbrli:xbrl.in-capmkt:DescribeTheMechanismsToReceive:
We have established a comprehensive grievance redressal framework that extends beyond employees to include
suppliers, farmers, local communities, and other stakeholders who may be affected by our operations. We maintain
continuous engagement with these groups through site-level interactions and community outreach programs, ensuring
their concerns are heard and addressed in a timely and transparent manner.
} Email: wecare@patanjalifoods.co.in
} Telephone and postal communication
Online contact form available at:
} www.patanjalifoods.com/ContactUs.php
All submissions are systematically tracked and resolved through an internal governance structure that ensures timely
escalation, review, and closure.
